avgDegree = d3.mean(mc1.nodes.map(node => getDegree(node.id, mc1)))
degreemap = {
const links = mc1.links;
const degrees = new Map();

links.forEach(link => {
degrees.set(link.source, (degrees.get(link.source) || 0) + 1);
degrees.set(link.target, (degrees.get(link.target) || 0) + 1);
});

return degrees;
}
degreeArray = Array.from(degreemap, ([id, degree]) => ({id, degree}))
minDegree = Math.min(...degreeArray.map(d => d.degree));
maxDegree = Math.max(...degreeArray.map(d => d.degree));

marks: [
Plot.boxX(degreeArray, {x: "degree", y: "count", sort: {y: "x"}})
]
})

getDegree = (nodeId, mc1) => {
return mc1.links.filter(link => (link.source === nodeId || link.target === nodeId)).length;
}
getStrength = (nodeId, mc1) => {
return mc1.links
.filter(link => (link.source === nodeId || link.target === nodeId))
.reduce((sum, link) => sum + link.weight, 0);
}
getAverageWeight = (nodeId, mc1) => {
const nodeLinks = mc1.links.filter(link => (link.source === nodeId || link.target === nodeId));
if (nodeLinks.length === 0) return 0;
return nodeLinks.reduce((sum, link) => sum + link.weight, 0) / nodeLinks.length;
}
getConnectionTypes = (nodeId, mc1) => {
const connectionTypes = {};
mc1.links
.filter(link => (link.source === nodeId || link.target === nodeId))
.forEach(link => {
if (!connectionTypes[link.type]) connectionTypes[link.type] = 0;
connectionTypes[link.type]++;
});
return connectionTypes;
}
logNodeStats = (nodeId, mc1) => {
return {
node: mc1.nodes.find(node => node.id === nodeId),
degree: getDegree(nodeId, mc1),
strength: getStrength(nodeId, mc1),
averageWeight: getAverageWeight(nodeId, mc1),
connectionTypes: getConnectionTypes(nodeId, mc1),
};
}
logNodeStats('Mar de la Vida OJSC', mc1);
logNodeStats(979893388, mc1);
logNodeStats("Oceanfront Oasis Inc Carriers", mc1);
logNodeStats(8327, mc1);
